wikipedia_page.main: Graham Hicks (born 15 November 1985 in Morecambe, Lancashire) is an English strongman competitor who placed second in the 2014 and 2018 Britain's Strongest Man competitions. Hicks is the 2019 Britain's Strongest man.

Graham Hicks of the UK withdrew the day before the competition began, and was replaced by Ervin Toots of Estonia. As a result, Gavin Bilton of the UK was moved from group 5 to group 1, and Toots took Bilton's place in group 5.
